1
00:00:05,667 --> 00:00:08,363
<i>Press down hard on the gas</i>

2
00:00:08,436 --> 00:00:12,304
<i>That's right, there's no compromise</i>

3
00:00:12,374 --> 00:00:16,367
<i>We'll slip through the night</i>

4
00:00:16,711 --> 00:00:19,202
<i>At the final moment push hard</i>

5
00:00:19,281 --> 00:00:23,342
<i>That's right, all the way to zero,</i>

6
00:00:23,418 --> 00:00:27,377
<i>Until we wipe away the days</i>

7
00:00:28,857 --> 00:00:33,590
<i>Gently open your heart</i>

8
00:00:34,296 --> 00:00:37,265
<i>If you pull it close to you</i>

9
00:00:39,701 --> 00:00:41,794
<i>It will reach you, without a doubt</i>

10
00:00:42,537 --> 00:00:43,834
<i>It will come, closer</i>

11
00:00:44,172 --> 00:00:46,732
<i>Now</i>

12
00:00:54,783 --> 00:01:00,153
<i>We're speeding through life,</i>
<i>squeezing it for all of its worth</i>

13
00:01:00,355 --> 00:01:01,515
<i>Our feet are tied</i>

14
00:01:01,589 --> 00:01:05,389
<i>But we still keep going farther</i>

15
00:01:05,727 --> 00:01:10,926
<i>Even if I take it back, and grasp it</i>

16
00:01:11,199 --> 00:01:12,530
<i>If you're not the one</i>

17
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:13,999
<i>There will be no meaning</i>

18
00:01:14,069 --> 00:01:20,338
<i>And so we'll go far off into the distance.</i>

19
00:01:47,831 --> 00:01:48,695
<i>If "Heaven" does not exist,</i>

20
00:01:48,766 --> 00:01:50,427
<i>enrich your knowledge,</i>
<i>and prepare for the chance.</i>

21
00:01:50,501 --> 00:01:51,399
<i>If "Earth" does not exist,</i>

22
00:01:51,468 --> 00:01:53,026
<i>run the fields in search</i>
<i>of an advantage.</i>

23
00:01:53,504 --> 00:01:57,167
<i>Open the series of Heaven and Earth,</i>
<i>and the perilous way shall be redressed...</i>

24
00:01:57,374 --> 00:02:01,902
<i>This is namely the secret of</i>
<i>"the one that guides..."</i>

25
00:02:02,679 --> 00:02:03,805
What's that?

26
00:02:04,281 --> 00:02:06,476
It probably has to do with the scroll.

27
00:02:07,451 --> 00:02:11,615
I think this means we're supposed
to open the Heaven & Earth scroll.

28
00:02:24,768 --> 00:02:26,793
Okay then, I'm going to open it.

29
00:02:38,482 --> 00:02:40,814
Huh? What's this?

30
00:02:41,485 --> 00:02:42,349
A man...?

31
00:02:42,419 --> 00:02:43,545
A person...?

32
00:02:48,125 --> 00:02:50,320
This is... a Summoning Jutsu!

33
00:02:50,627 --> 00:02:53,494
Naruto! Sakura!
Let go of the scroll!

34
00:02:53,664 --> 00:02:54,460
Oh...

35
00:03:06,210 --> 00:03:07,268
Wha?!

36
00:03:07,377 --> 00:03:09,140
Y-You...

37
00:03:18,188 --> 00:03:19,280
Hi!

38
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:22,156
It's been a long time.

39
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:30,063
<i>Surviving the Cut!</i>
<i>The Rookie Nine Together Again!</i>

40
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:38,037
W-What's going on?

41
00:03:38,375 --> 00:03:41,742
It appears you guys have had
a rough time of it.

42
00:03:41,812 --> 00:03:42,972
What?!

43
00:03:43,313 --> 00:03:46,908
Why are you appearing with
a Summoning?

44
00:03:47,184 --> 00:03:49,152
At the end of this second exam,

45
00:03:49,219 --> 00:03:53,019
we Chunin are to
welcome the test takers.

46
00:03:53,757 --> 00:03:55,486
I just happened to be given

47
00:03:55,559 --> 00:03:58,722
the important task of being
the messenger for you guys.

48
00:03:59,529 --> 00:04:00,928
Messenger...?!

49
00:04:05,202 --> 00:04:07,727
Just in time.

50
00:04:10,274 --> 00:04:11,104
Everyone...

51
00:04:12,476 --> 00:04:15,536
Congratulations on surviving
the second exam.

52
00:04:17,781 --> 00:04:19,305
To celebrate your passing,

53
00:04:19,383 --> 00:04:22,875
I'd like to treat you to
some Ichiraku ramen, but...

54
00:04:22,953 --> 00:04:25,387
Ohh... Cool!

55
00:04:25,455 --> 00:04:26,444
Uh oh...

56
00:04:26,924 --> 00:04:27,982
H-Hey, Naruto!

57
00:04:28,358 --> 00:04:30,155
- Listen to the end...
- Cool! Cool!

58
00:04:30,827 --> 00:04:34,024
Ramen! Ramen!
Believe it!

59
00:04:34,731 --> 00:04:37,564
I've done great job!
I'm the greatest!

60
00:04:37,634 --> 00:04:40,501
I so want to eat ramen!
Believe it!

61
00:04:41,905 --> 00:04:43,463
He's got so much energy.

62
00:04:44,608 --> 00:04:45,575
Yaaaay!

63
00:04:45,642 --> 00:04:46,700
Shut up!

64
00:04:47,311 --> 00:04:52,248
Man, that scatterbrained part
of you is the same as always, eh.

65
00:04:54,451 --> 00:04:55,645
I see.

66
00:04:55,852 --> 00:04:56,546
Huh?

67
00:04:57,187 --> 00:05:00,281
If we had looked at the scroll
in the middle of the exam,

68
00:05:00,891 --> 00:05:04,520
what were you going to do, Iruka Sensei?

69
00:05:08,198 --> 00:05:11,827
Sasuke, you're a sharp one,
as usual.

70
00:05:14,304 --> 00:05:16,033
You guessed right.

71
00:05:16,406 --> 00:05:22,174
The rules of this exam were to test
your conclusive mission execution ability.

72
00:05:22,913 --> 00:05:24,278
To put it simply,

73
00:05:24,348 --> 00:05:29,376
in the case of the scrolls being opened
contrary to the rules...

74
00:05:29,553 --> 00:05:31,453
In the case of them being opened...?

75
00:05:36,059 --> 00:05:41,156
I was ordered to knock unconscious
the test takers in front of me

76
00:05:41,231 --> 00:05:43,961
until the end of the exam.

77
00:05:45,569 --> 00:05:48,094
Good thing you didn't open the scroll.

78
00:05:50,207 --> 00:05:52,505
Kabuto, thank you!

79
00:05:53,343 --> 00:05:54,503
Phew!

80
00:05:54,745 --> 00:05:57,145
That was seriously close...

81
00:06:00,017 --> 00:06:01,450
Oh yeah, Sensei!

82
00:06:01,518 --> 00:06:02,450
Huh?

83
00:06:02,753 --> 00:06:05,153
By the way,
what're the letters on that wall?

84
00:06:05,288 --> 00:06:07,779
They're kind of vermiculated and

85
00:06:07,858 --> 00:06:10,349
we don't understand
their meaning at all.

86
00:06:11,595 --> 00:06:13,495
Never mind, never mind!

87
00:06:13,563 --> 00:06:15,463
We passed!

88
00:06:15,832 --> 00:06:21,236
No... explaining that is
one more of my duties.

89
00:06:21,772 --> 00:06:24,002
What, really?

90
00:06:24,074 --> 00:06:26,201
I'm saying that's right.

91
00:06:27,744 --> 00:06:28,904
Give it a read.

92
00:06:29,946 --> 00:06:33,609
These are Chunin instructions
Master Hokage recorded.

93
00:06:34,117 --> 00:06:35,448
Instructions?!

94
00:06:35,819 --> 00:06:36,649
That's right!

95
00:06:36,887 --> 00:06:40,789
Heaven in this text
refers to the human head.

96
00:06:41,091 --> 00:06:43,286
Earth refers to the human body.

97
00:06:44,194 --> 00:06:45,320
No kidding...

98
00:06:45,562 --> 00:06:46,927
<i>If "Heaven" does not exist,</i>

99
00:06:46,997 --> 00:06:49,830
<i>enrich your knowledge,</i>
<i>and prepare for the chance.</i>

100
00:06:50,067 --> 00:06:51,329
In other words...

101
00:06:52,069 --> 00:06:55,197
If your weaknesses are
inside your head, Naruto...

102
00:06:55,605 --> 00:06:58,870
learn various logics in
preparing for your missions.

103
00:06:59,076 --> 00:07:01,340
Hah! So meddlesome!

104
00:07:02,679 --> 00:07:04,670
<i>If "Earth" does not exist,</i>

105
00:07:04,781 --> 00:07:07,306
<i>run through the fields</i>
<i>in search of an advantage.</i>

106
00:07:07,584 --> 00:07:10,485
If your weaknesses are in
your physical strength, Sakura,

107
00:07:10,654 --> 00:07:16,183
it means you must not
slack off on your daily training.

108
00:07:18,295 --> 00:07:21,890
And if you combine both
Heaven and Earth...

109
00:07:22,265 --> 00:07:24,733
Any perilous mission is the right way...

110
00:07:25,068 --> 00:07:25,966
In other words...

111
00:07:26,069 --> 00:07:30,506
what can also be called a rule
of might and become a safe mission.

112
00:07:30,841 --> 00:07:33,503
Then, what about
the spot with the missing letter?

113
00:07:34,744 --> 00:07:37,269
The letter refers to Chunin.

114
00:07:38,081 --> 00:07:43,075
The one letter for "person" that
was in the scroll from earlier goes there.

115
00:07:44,087 --> 00:07:45,952
These five days of survival
were to test

116
00:07:46,022 --> 00:07:49,583
the test-takers' fundamental
abilities as Chunin.

117
00:07:50,594 --> 00:07:53,154
And you guys cleared it in fine style.

118
00:07:54,431 --> 00:07:56,331
Chunin is of unit leader class.

119
00:07:56,566 --> 00:07:58,727
They have the responsibility
of leading a team.

120
00:07:59,436 --> 00:08:02,337
Be more deeply aware of
the necessity of physical strength...

121
00:08:02,706 --> 00:08:06,540
and knowledge in missions!

122
00:08:07,310 --> 00:08:10,507
I want you to take on
the next step,

123
00:08:10,580 --> 00:08:12,673
never forgetting these
Chunin instructions.

124
00:08:13,917 --> 00:08:17,944
That is all of the messenger task
I was given.

125
00:08:21,024 --> 00:08:22,082
Got it!

126
00:08:31,768 --> 00:08:32,666
Huh?

127
00:08:36,273 --> 00:08:41,609
But, as for the final third exam,
don't push it too far.

128
00:08:42,445 --> 00:08:43,969
Especially you, Naruto.

129
00:08:44,047 --> 00:08:45,981
- You're the biggest worry...
- Iruka Sensei.

130
00:08:46,316 --> 00:08:48,876
From when I received the
Leaf headband,

131
00:08:48,952 --> 00:08:52,251
I was no longer
an Academy student, you know?!

132
00:08:52,589 --> 00:08:54,250
There's nothing to worry!
Believe it!

133
00:08:55,458 --> 00:09:00,157
Also, this is the proof you
gave me that I'm full fledged, right?!

134
00:09:00,330 --> 00:09:03,629
That I'm scatterbrained may
not have changed,

135
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:05,964
but I'm not a kid anymore!

136
00:09:08,505 --> 00:09:09,631
I'm now...

137
00:09:13,043 --> 00:09:14,772
A Ninja!

138
00:09:23,587 --> 00:09:24,451
I see.

139
00:09:24,521 --> 00:09:26,386
I'm sorry, Naruto.

140
00:09:30,727 --> 00:09:33,958
<i>I know their strength the best.</i>

141
00:09:34,064 --> 00:09:35,429
<i>If it's futile anyway,</i>

142
00:09:35,498 --> 00:09:37,432
<i>I would like to give them</i>
<i>the final word personally.</i>

143
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:41,903
<i>If you're that hung up on it,</i>
<i>I can leave that team to you.</i>

144
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:46,368
<i>To think you'd play the devil's advocate...</i>

145
00:09:47,244 --> 00:09:48,506
<i>Thank you very much.</i>

146
00:09:49,379 --> 00:09:52,246
<i>But, they're Kakashi's, right?</i>

147
00:09:53,316 --> 00:09:55,511
<i>If he's the one who</i>
<i>recommended them,</i>

148
00:09:55,585 --> 00:09:58,213
<i>I thought I could count on them.</i>

149
00:10:02,926 --> 00:10:04,257
<i>Stay out of it!</i>

150
00:10:04,594 --> 00:10:10,226
<i>They're not your students anymore.</i>
<i>They're my subordinates now.</i>

151
00:10:16,373 --> 00:10:19,342
<i>The one who might truly understand</i>

152
00:10:21,811 --> 00:10:25,508
<i>the strength of these kids.</i>
<i>Might be you, Kakashi.</i>

153
00:10:34,291 --> 00:10:35,417
How is it?

154
00:10:35,825 --> 00:10:37,884
Does the Curse Mark still hurt?

155
00:10:38,194 --> 00:10:39,092
No.

156
00:10:39,229 --> 00:10:41,322
Thanks to you,
it's gotten quite a bit better.

157
00:10:42,499 --> 00:10:48,267
Anyway, Orochimaru is one
of those three legendary Leaf Ninjas, right?

158
00:10:48,705 --> 00:10:50,935
He's a S rank bingo book
rouge Shinobi

159
00:10:51,007 --> 00:10:53,737
who even the Anbu couldn't touch, right?

160
00:10:54,844 --> 00:10:57,005
I heard that he'd already died, but...

161
00:10:57,113 --> 00:11:00,879
Why'd he come to this village now...?

162
00:11:09,793 --> 00:11:11,727
<i>There's a kid I want, you see.</i>

163
00:11:14,097 --> 00:11:17,965
<i>This kid inherits the abilities</i>
<i>of the Uchiha clan, so...</i>

164
00:11:23,039 --> 00:11:23,869
It's...

165
00:11:24,874 --> 00:11:26,239
It's probably Sasuke, right?

166
00:11:26,609 --> 00:11:27,405
Huh?!

167
00:11:28,311 --> 00:11:29,608
<i>Master Anko!</i>

168
00:11:30,347 --> 00:11:33,339
<i>Twenty one second exam</i>
<i>finishers have been confirmed.</i>

169
00:11:34,250 --> 00:11:36,980
<i>As for the third exam, according</i>
<i>to the regulations of the Chunin Exams,</i>

170
00:11:37,053 --> 00:11:39,146
<i>preliminaries are planned for</i>
<i>the first time in five years.</i>

171
00:11:40,023 --> 00:11:41,650
<i>The second exam is over.</i>

172
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:53,833
For the time being
continue the exams as is,

173
00:11:53,903 --> 00:11:57,168
but while keeping
an eye on his movements.

174
00:11:57,674 --> 00:11:58,265
Yes...

175
00:12:11,790 --> 00:12:15,089
First off, congratulations on
finishing the second exam.

176
00:12:17,262 --> 00:12:20,322
<i>There were seventy eight</i>
<i>test takers for the second exam.</i>

177
00:12:20,565 --> 00:12:23,261
<i>To think twenty one have</i>
<i>made it this far.</i>

178
00:12:23,802 --> 00:12:28,034
<i>I said to make it less than half,</i>
<i>but I'd really thought about single digits.</i>

179
00:12:41,686 --> 00:12:43,210
I'm hungry!

180
00:12:43,288 --> 00:12:45,449
There are still this many remaining?

181
00:12:45,824 --> 00:12:47,155
This is such a major pain.

182
00:12:49,494 --> 00:12:51,689
Sasuke and others have passed, too.

183
00:12:52,330 --> 00:12:53,592
Of course...

184
00:12:58,503 --> 00:13:00,562
We went to that much trouble
to save them...

185
00:13:00,772 --> 00:13:03,536
It'd all be for naught if they didn't pass.

186
00:13:07,212 --> 00:13:09,806
Your team didn't do too bad.

187
00:13:10,715 --> 00:13:12,512
I guess they were lucky.

188
00:13:13,151 --> 00:13:17,144
But as long as my team is around,
they can't go any higher.

189
00:13:17,489 --> 00:13:19,957
After all, whether you
like it or not,

190
00:13:20,025 --> 00:13:22,084
ability talks at the next barrier.

191
00:13:22,260 --> 00:13:24,888
Well, adolescence can sometimes
be bittersweet and

192
00:13:24,963 --> 00:13:27,193
can sometimes be harsh, Kakashi...

193
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:30,131
Did you say something?

194
00:13:30,201 --> 00:13:34,934
<i>Oh my God!</i>

195
00:13:37,709 --> 00:13:40,337
<i>Not bad, my rival Kakashi.</i>

196
00:13:40,545 --> 00:13:44,845
<i>But that part of you is so hip...</i>
<i>which is what annoys me!</i>

197
00:13:45,317 --> 00:13:48,878
<i>So that's Guy Sensei's eternal rival, eh?</i>

198
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:52,283
<i>Guy Sensei totally loses visually...</i>

199
00:13:52,424 --> 00:13:56,383
<i>Guy Sensei is the hippest</i>
<i>of all the teachers!</i>

200
00:13:56,561 --> 00:13:57,585
<i>He shines!</i>

201
00:13:57,696 --> 00:13:58,458
<i>Okay!</i>

202
00:13:59,164 --> 00:14:03,294
Please watch, Guy Sensei!
I'll shine, too!

203
00:14:16,748 --> 00:14:23,449
<i>I don't ever want to see</i>
<i>tears of those dear to me again.</i>

204
00:14:24,689 --> 00:14:25,553
<i>So...</i>

205
00:14:26,891 --> 00:14:29,257
<i>I won't ever lose again!</i>

206
00:14:29,327 --> 00:14:30,294
<i>Guy Sensei.</i>

207
00:14:31,129 --> 00:14:33,620
<i>Sure enough, the outstanding candidates</i>
<i>have gathered.</i>

208
00:14:37,769 --> 00:14:39,600
<i>Sasuke Uchiha, eh?</i>

209
00:14:43,375 --> 00:14:46,902
<i>I'll get you back for my arms,</i>
<i>Sasuke Uchiha...</i>

210
00:14:47,679 --> 00:14:48,941
<i>At any cost.</i>

211
00:15:00,658 --> 00:15:04,617
<i>To think a mere seven teams</i>
<i>are left of the twenty six...</i>

212
00:15:07,232 --> 00:15:10,395
<i>Sure enough, Gaara is unhurt.</i>

213
00:15:13,738 --> 00:15:15,365
<i>Akamaru's acting strange...</i>

214
00:15:21,012 --> 00:15:22,411
<i>Those Sand Village guys...</i>

215
00:15:25,183 --> 00:15:27,083
<i>Naruto passed, too.</i>

216
00:15:28,319 --> 00:15:29,308
<i>Thank goodness...</i>

217
00:15:30,488 --> 00:15:33,355
What, all the Leaf Village
rookies are here.

218
00:15:33,525 --> 00:15:35,117
Say! Say!

219
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:39,319
Old man Hokage and Iruka Sensei and
even Intense Brow are here. Believe it!

220
00:15:39,497 --> 00:15:41,692
It feels like everyone's assembled.

221
00:15:42,267 --> 00:15:45,828
Humph... I don't have a very good feeling.

222
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:51,572
<i>To think this many are left...</i>

223
00:15:52,010 --> 00:15:55,002
<i>Moreover, of those left, almost all are rookies...</i>

224
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:59,281
<i>So that's why they fought</i>
<i>in recommending them.</i>

225
00:16:00,151 --> 00:16:03,018
Now then, we will now have
the explanation of the third exam

226
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:04,486
from Master Hokage.

227
00:16:04,589 --> 00:16:06,682
Listen carefully, everybody!

228
00:16:07,592 --> 00:16:09,787
Now then, if you will,
Master Hokage.

229
00:16:10,662 --> 00:16:11,458
All right.

230
00:16:18,436 --> 00:16:23,567
Before the explanation of
the third exam that we will start from now,

231
00:16:23,641 --> 00:16:28,078
I have just one thing I want
to tell everyone flat out.

232
00:16:30,148 --> 00:16:33,481
About the true purpose of these exams.

233
00:16:33,818 --> 00:16:35,251
<i>True purpose...?!</i>

234
00:16:35,753 --> 00:16:40,588
Why do allied nations conduct
the exams on a conjoint basis?

235
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:42,724
Huh?

236
00:16:43,261 --> 00:16:48,221
Raising the levels of the shinobi
and friendship among allied nations.

237
00:16:48,299 --> 00:16:51,996
It won't do to have the wrong idea
of the true meaning of that statement.

238
00:16:52,170 --> 00:16:54,434
These exams are so to speak...

239
00:16:54,639 --> 00:16:55,867
<i>So to speak...?</i>

240
00:17:04,849 --> 00:17:08,114
A microcosm of battle
between allied nations.

241
00:17:09,888 --> 00:17:11,048
What does that mean?

242
00:17:12,257 --> 00:17:14,088
If we look back on history,

243
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:16,991
the allied nations of today were
once neighboring nations

244
00:17:17,061 --> 00:17:21,828
that continued to vie with
each other and battle for power.

245
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:27,669
In order to avoid a futile crushing
of each others' military strength,

246
00:17:27,739 --> 00:17:30,640
those nations mutually selected
a place to battle.

247
00:17:30,742 --> 00:17:36,009
And that was how the
Chunin Exams originally began.

248
00:17:39,984 --> 00:17:43,545
W-Why do we have
to do such a thing?

249
00:17:43,922 --> 00:17:46,550
We're not doing this to
select Chunins?!

250
00:17:46,958 --> 00:17:53,227
There is no question that these exams
are to select Shinobi

251
00:17:53,298 --> 00:17:55,732
worthy of becoming,"Chunin."

252
00:17:57,035 --> 00:17:58,593
But on the other hand,

253
00:17:58,670 --> 00:18:01,138
these exams also provide a venue

254
00:18:01,205 --> 00:18:05,972
for Shinobi who carry their nation's pride
on their backs to fight for their lives!

255
00:18:06,711 --> 00:18:08,372
Nation's pride?

256
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:13,512
Many feudal lords and those of
prominence from many nations

257
00:18:13,585 --> 00:18:19,387
who request Shinobi for work
are invited to this third exam as guests.

258
00:18:20,725 --> 00:18:23,990
And, the feudal lords and
Head Ninja of each Village

259
00:18:24,062 --> 00:18:28,260
of the nations will watch your battles.

260
00:18:29,267 --> 00:18:31,360
If the gap in national power
becomes unbridgeable,

261
00:18:31,436 --> 00:18:34,405
the strong nations are inundated
with job requests.

262
00:18:35,106 --> 00:18:39,440
The requests of nations deemed
weak, on the other hand, decline.

263
00:18:39,877 --> 00:18:41,071
And therewithal,

264
00:18:41,145 --> 00:18:47,744
we can exert pressure upon
each neighboring nation...

265
00:18:47,819 --> 00:18:52,119
That is to say, just how much military
strength our Village is developing and has.

266
00:18:52,690 --> 00:18:56,387
Even so, why is it necessary for
us to fight for our lives?!

267
00:18:57,996 --> 00:19:00,396
The nation's strength is
the Village's strength.

268
00:19:00,465 --> 00:19:03,093
The Village's strength is
the Shinobi's strength.

269
00:19:03,735 --> 00:19:09,640
And the true strength of the Shinobi
is created only in a fight for one's life!

270
00:19:10,575 --> 00:19:15,410
This exam is a place to see
the strength of home country Shinobi,

271
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:17,471
and a place to display this as well.

272
00:19:17,915 --> 00:19:21,476
It is because it's an exam where
you truly fight for your life

273
00:19:21,552 --> 00:19:22,678
that this has meaning

274
00:19:22,754 --> 00:19:26,884
It's for this very reason that
your forerunners fought in this exam,

275
00:19:26,958 --> 00:19:29,950
a dream worth striving for.

276
00:19:32,330 --> 00:19:36,061
Then why...
use the expression "friendship"?!

277
00:19:37,068 --> 00:19:39,559
I said it at the start, didn't I?!

278
00:19:39,637 --> 00:19:43,004
That it won't do for you to have
the wrong idea of the meaning

279
00:19:43,307 --> 00:19:49,246
It's a custom where balance is
preserved by fighting and removing life.

280
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:51,304
This is the friendship
of the Shinobi world.

281
00:19:51,382 --> 00:19:53,850
This is a fight for life with
the pride of the village and

282
00:19:53,918 --> 00:19:56,944
one's own dream on the line.

283
00:20:04,095 --> 00:20:06,791
Heh, I'm convinced.

284
00:20:07,331 --> 00:20:08,662
Anything is fine.

285
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:14,063
Just tell us the content of
that fight-for-life test.

286
00:20:14,439 --> 00:20:14,996
Very well.

287
00:20:15,173 --> 00:20:20,338
Now then, this is where I'd like to
explain the third exam.

288
00:20:20,411 --> 00:20:21,139
But actually...

289
00:20:25,650 --> 00:20:31,282
Master Hokage, please allow me,
Hayate Gekko,

290
00:20:31,355 --> 00:20:33,823
who was given the task of judging,
to speak first.

291
00:20:33,925 --> 00:20:35,324
I leave it to you...

292
00:20:36,661 --> 00:20:38,128
Nice to meet you, everyone...

293
00:20:41,532 --> 00:20:44,433
Umm, there's something...
I'd like you all to do...

294
00:20:46,137 --> 00:20:47,900
before the third exam.

295
00:21:05,772 --> 00:21:10,368
<i>Hey, can you hear it?</i>

296
00:21:10,477 --> 00:21:18,577
<i>The clear, blue sky goes on and on</i>

297
00:21:19,652 --> 00:21:28,185
<i>The ocean spans limitlessly</i>

298
00:21:28,795 --> 00:21:36,497
<i>Please keep that smile on your face forever</i>

299
00:21:37,904 --> 00:21:43,433
<i>Or else I'll cry</i>

300
00:21:43,510 --> 00:21:47,276
<i>You won't have to search around you</i>

301
00:21:47,347 --> 00:21:50,908
<i>It's all ok now.</i>

302
00:21:51,384 --> 00:21:59,792
<i>Everyone is inside</i>
<i>this hand</i>

303
00:22:00,193 --> 00:22:05,256
<i>when you want to cry, and you want to run away</i>

304
00:22:05,331 --> 00:22:09,734
<i>When you forget what happiness is</i>

305
00:22:09,903 --> 00:22:13,566
<i>Just sing.</i>

306
00:22:13,873 --> 00:22:18,970
<i>Light is born, and darkness was born</i>

307
00:22:19,112 --> 00:22:21,239
<i>The two are one</i>

308
00:22:21,347 --> 00:22:27,616
<i>Harmonia, feel the telepathy</i>

309
00:22:28,221 --> 00:22:33,215
<i>Hey, can you hear it?</i>

310
00:22:37,905 --> 00:22:40,533
What's the idea?
Sudden preliminaries?

311
00:22:41,141 --> 00:22:44,440
Didn't we just get to the tower?
Also, something's wrong with Sasuke.

312
00:22:44,978 --> 00:22:47,947
It's too much for you, Sasuke!
Please, drop out!

313
00:22:48,182 --> 00:22:50,446
You're in no condition
to fight properly!

314
00:22:50,517 --> 00:22:52,712
No matter what you say,

315
00:22:52,786 --> 00:22:54,754
I'm going to tell the teachers
about that bruise.

316
00:22:55,522 --> 00:22:59,856
Next episode: "Narrowing the Field:
Sudden Death Elimination!"

317
00:23:00,227 --> 00:23:02,161
Sasuke, I'm scared.
